    "summary": "BACKGROUND:\n22 year experience as Principal Design Architect and Project Manager on a variety of small, medium and major pharmaceutical capital projects: new facilities, upgrade and expansion of existing facilities; oral solid dose (OSD) and small volume parental (SVP) sterile injectables.\nPerformed the full life cycle of concept, detail and technical design and project and quality control management, from inception and concept of projects, to construction, final completion and handover for validation, commissioning, regulatory review and manufacturing.  \nProjects executed in compliance with international GMP standards (US FDA, EU, UK MCA, WHO, Aus TGA).  \nCareer project costs valued in excess of \u20ac 145 000 000.\nPROFESSIONAL WORK EXPERIENCE:\nFast track design, management and administration, in conjunction with the client, with and as a member of a Project Team comprising pharmaceutical specialists, process equipment specialists and suppliers, process engineers, commissioning, qualification and validation specialists, service providers, professional consultants team, main contractors, and direct and specialist sub-contractors.\nAll projects were time, cost and quality driven.\nProjects were skillfully executed and completed within the budget and program via four work stages of specialized design, project management and quality management deliverables.  \nWORK STAGES:\nWork Stage 1: Project Inception, Concept Design and Viability.  \nWork Stage 2: Detail Design and Documentation.\nWork Stage 3: Construction and Coordination.\nWork Stage 4: Close-out.\n\nResume available on request.",
